"Private Proof-of-Stake Blockchains using Differentially-Private Stake Distortion.","4","13. Let 𝑝𝑣= 𝑞( 𝑓𝑣), 𝜂= max ␀𝑞−1(𝑝𝑣± 𝜏), and 𝛿= 𝑂( 1 log𝑛), then (i) the random walk of RdBin exits at the correct node with constant failure probability; and (ii) the inference error is bounded by max( 𝜃 𝑆,𝜂). 1592    32nd USENIX Security Symposium USENIX Association Proof. At each step of the random walk, the proba-bility of moving in the wrong direction is 𝑂( 1 log𝑛). As such, by union bound, the overall failure proba-bility is 𝑂(1). If the random walk exits correctly, it must have either reached a leaf node or an inter-val [ 𝑓𝑎, 𝑓𝑏] where |𝑞( ˆ𝑓= 𝑓𝑎+ 𝑓𝑏 2 ) −𝑞( 𝑓𝑣)| < 𝜏, indicat-ing that the minimum comparison threshold has been met. For the first case, since | 𝑓𝑎−𝑓𝑏| = 𝜃 𝑆, thus the inference error must be bounded by 𝜃 𝑆. For the sec-ond case, it is clear that the error must be smaller than max ␀|𝑞−1(𝑝𝑣+ 𝜏) −𝑓𝑣|, |𝑞−1(𝑝𝑣−𝜏) −𝑓𝑣|. □ B.3 Proof of Theorem 3 Proof. (Theorem 3) Consider party 𝑃𝑖and let 𝑆𝑖= {𝑠𝑖 1,𝑠𝑖 2,...,𝑠𝑖 𝑡} to be the stake history of 𝑃𝑖. Given 𝑆𝑡= {𝑠1,𝑠2,...,𝑠𝑡} and 𝑆′ 𝑡= {𝑠′ 1,𝑠′ 2,...,𝑠′ 𝑡} to be a pair of (𝛼,𝑢)-neighbor stake profiles. Let 𝑥, 𝑦∈R such that 𝑥≤𝑦≤𝑥+ 𝛼, and by definition of (𝛼,𝑢)-neighbor we have 𝑠𝑢= 𝑥, 𝑠′ 𝑢= 𝑦. We also consider a given out-put 𝑜⊂𝑅𝑎𝑛𝑔𝑒(Lkg) and next. we compute the fol-lowing probabilities (Note that we simplify the term Pr  Lkg⟨𝑃𝑖,𝑆⟩= 𝑜  as a conditional probability Pr [𝑜| 𝑆]) Pr  𝑜| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑠𝑢  ≤max 𝑆𝑡Pr [𝑜| 𝑆𝑡] × ∑︁ 𝑆𝑡⊂S Pr  𝑆𝑡| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑥  Pr  𝑜| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑠′ 𝑢  ≥min 𝑆′ 𝑡 Pr  𝑜| 𝑆′ 𝑡  × ∑︁ 𝑆′ 𝑡⊂S Pr  𝑆′ 𝑡| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑦  Note that any stake dataset 𝑆⊂S is a (𝛼,𝑢)-neighbor of itself. Thus it holds that Í 𝑆𝑡⊂S Pr  𝑆𝑡| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑥  ≤ Í 𝑆′ 𝑡⊂S Pr  𝑆′ 𝑡| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑦  , since for any 𝑆𝑡there exists at least one (𝛼,𝑢)-neighbor 𝑆′ 𝑡. In addition, by Definition 5.3, we know that max𝑆𝑡Pr [𝑜| 𝑆𝑡] ≤𝑒𝜔(𝑡−𝑢) ×min𝑆′ 𝑡Pr  𝑜| 𝑆′ 𝑡  . Thus by combing the two facts, we can conclude that: Pr  𝑜| 𝑠𝑖 𝑢= 𝑠𝑢  Pr  𝑜| 𝑠𝑖𝑢= 𝑠′𝑢  ≤ Í 𝑆𝑡⊂S Pr  𝑆𝑡| 𝑠𝑖